Syntax: readaura <target>

Psychically read the aura of a living target in your room, revealing
their true race and power level to you alone. This pierces disguises:
it works even on someone currently displaying as another race or
shielded by an appearance override, and even if you have never
introduced, been introduced, or remembered them.

The reading never reveals the target's name. It refers to them only
as "they" or "their true nature".

This is a one-time read, not a relationship change. It does not add
the target to your known list and shows nothing to anyone else in the
room.

Costs ISP (read aura power). Target by whatever word finds them in the
room (their name, or an identifying word if they are an NPC), the same
as look or kill. The generic 'psi'/'cast' dispatch commands require a
known target and will refuse a stranger, so always use readaura
directly.

See also: psi, psionics, remoteview, introduce, remember, known
